  }, "Noise-less"), mdx("p", null, "The second interesting feature of this problem is that we are effectively dealing with a problem that has no noise \u2013 a case of [", "[transductive-learning]", "] if there ever was one. That is, there is no desire or need for \"generalising\", as the data distribution is the population, and there is no chance for \"dataset drift\". Interpolation is king."), mdx(Note, {
